://pub35.ezboard.com/ulerkinbehinja.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lerkin Behinja</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/26/02 11:33:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23487.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> EQ2 - Rebirth of the Rogue class</span><hr size=1>      By now everyone knows that EverQuest 2 is in the works.  It is FAR from completion and probably just starting real development.  With that in mind, what SHOULD the EQ 2 Rogue class be?  This is your chance for what might have been in EQ1 to come to fruition in EQ2.<br><br>Post your comments/suggestions. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ushariin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shariin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/26/02 12:08:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23487.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ2 - Rebirth of the Rogue class</span><hr size=1> Athletic, acrobatic, lithe.  Doesn't rely on raw power to accomplish tasks, but on manual and intellectual dexterity, outwitting one's opponents as they run circles around them.  Able to run faster, jump further and climb higher.  Wouldn't wear jangly chain or plate, and probably not restricting hard leathers either.<br><br>None of this turning invis junk.  Blending in to the environment, sure, walking around silently, sure.  Disguise, sure.  Not actually invisible.<br><br>In combat, more pure skill and less strength, in order to parry and dodge blows rather than take them on the chin.  Would probably try to land particularly painful blows, though not necessarily damaging ones - fight dirty.<br><br>Poisons, potions and other chemicals - smokebombs for instance.  Traps - laying tripwires and sprung traps.  *Real* lockpicking - have the ability to bash down locked doors or pick them, one of them being quiet and concealable.  The ability to open all those darn chests around the place.<br> <p><center> <table border="0" cellspacing="0" style="background-color: black;"> <tr><td colspan="3"><img src="http://ojaste.dhs.org/~shariin/Shariin.gif" alt="Shariin"></td></tr> <tr style="color: white; background: rgb(40,35,40); text-align: left; font: italic bold 10pt sans-serif;"> <td>Shariin Shadowblade</td> <td style="text-align: center; color: rgb(128,128,128);">House of Kindred</td> <td style="text-align: right;">Assassin</td> </tr> </table> </center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=miladas>Miladas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/26/02 12:16:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23487.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ2 - Rebirth of the Rogue class</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Athletic, acrobatic, lithe... The ability to open all those darn chests around the place.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>In other words, very much like the concepts in Thief II?<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.co