I'd like to say.  Rogues were fine as a chain class until Evade was nerfed and because rogues complained about taking more damage digusting AC was added to their gear.  Now...Below are some definitions for Rogue, Thief, and Assassin.  If you are looking for a defined class based on name...<br><br>rogue   Pronunciation Key  (rg)<br>n. <br>An unprincipled, deceitful, and unreliable person; a scoundrel or rascal. <br>One who is playfully mischievous; a scamp. <br>A wandering beggar; a vagrant. <br>A vicious and solitary animal, especially an elephant that has separated itself from its herd. <br>An organism, especially a plant, that shows an undesirable variation from a standard. <br><br>thief   Pronunciation Key  (thf)<br>n. pl. thieves (thvz) <br>One who steals, especially by stealth<br>Assassin<br><br>\As*sas&quot;sin\, n. One who kills, or attempts to kill, by surprise or secret assault; one who treacherously murders any one unprepared for defense. <br><br>What is my point?  Okay an Assassin is a pure murderer machine he doesn't care who or what he kills...All damage...All poison...Would be capable of doing incredible damage from any range.  A thief would not be a combat type at all.  They would just steal, and given VI's view on player theft that isn't going to happen.  Rogue, This is just someone who is either a loner or a bad guy.  VI basically stripped the rogue part tossed in a dash of thief then added just enough assassin to make a decent class.<br><br>Bottom line is EQ Rogues are not and will never be a rogue/thief/assassin by definition.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uqutsemnie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qutsemnie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/26/02 3:04:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23487.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ2 - Rebirth of the Rogue class</span><hr size=1> i want rogues(current form)/wizard/mez removed.<br><br>Ok your thinking how in hell can you want rogues removed?  Bear with me.  imagine EQ as it is.  Now blot out rogues and wizards.  Picture them gone.  Suddenly all the classes are balanced imo.  <br><br>Think about it.  Rogues and wizards are the two classes that seem to screw the entire system.  Why is that?  Becuase no class should be at its core about damage IMO.  <br><br>Consider shamans.  Are shamans balanced?  Who the hell knows?  really. they buff raids.  is that balanced?   its not parsable so its always balanced.  <br><br>Now picture druids with wizards gone.  They would be the only class with ports (would give them xlocs).  Are they then balanced?  Who the hell knows?  Its not parsable.<br><br>  IMO a class should be to complicated in its relationship to the other classes to have simple balance conversations.  that means tossing out any class that lives and dies by damage. <br><br>Cant think of a caster with a focus other then damage that would be interesting to a raid then dont put them in the game.  Cant think of a melee with a focus other then damage that would be interesting to a raid then dont put them in the game.  ok well thats a bit odd but you get me a little.  <br>Classes should not be balanced by: my melee class does 140% of your melees classes damage.  It should be balanced by &quot;all melees do 1.0 and have x intangibles of serious interest&quot;  I would have sooner seen rogues get casting (its a mythical rogue remember) when the developers were stumped then see them get to do a 140% of the damage a warrior does.  I think Diablo 2 demonstrated how that was a viable idea in a fantasy setting.  <br><br>I mean if that bull aside doesnt convince you then i stand with just imagine eq without rogues and wizards as it stands now and i think its balanced... but there going to fook with it somemore to &quot;balance&quot; it.<br><br>So rogues as we know them should die with eq1.  Same with wizards.  come back with more creative versions that only do as much damage as teh other classes not more.<br><br>As for mez... hehe just added it for completeness.  I think the game is much much more fun when you cant mez your mobs.  mez is fun for the enchanter.  off tanking/rooting/charming/kiting/fearing is fun for the whole family =)<br><br> <p><table width="350" border="0" bgcolor="#51260B"><tr bgcolor="#924614"><td width="125"><div align="center"><img src="http://www.geraldfield.com/nadinesplace/muppetquiz/oldguys.jpg" width="125" height="108"></div></td><td width="177" bgcolor="#924614"><p align="center"><b><font size="3" color="#381A07">You are Statler or Waldorf!</font></b><font color="#381A07"><br><font size="2">You don't like dealing with most people, preferring to ridicule other people along with your equally misanthropic friend.</font></font></p></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#51260B"><td colspan="2"><div align="center"><font size="1"><b><a href="http://www.geraldfield.com/cgi-bin/unofficial/quizzes/sfesurvey.cgi?whatmuppetareyou" target="_blank"><font color="#C26A30">Take the <i>What Muppet Are You?</i> Quiz!</font></a></b></font></div></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uchaidduskwalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chaid Duskwalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/26/02 3:09:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23487.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ2 - Rebirth of the Rogue class</span><hr size=1> Let's get down to specifics:<br><br>Sense Traps/Disarm 