ass=m><span class=title> Re: EQ2 - Rebirth of the Rogue class</span><hr size=1> Depends, really.<br><br>If they keep the game as an mob killing XP grind, a &quot;thief&quot; style character doesn't work.<br><br>/shrug.<br><br>Interesting idea tho, having a &quot;fixed&quot; DPS for all melee classes.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utenoroallegro.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tenoro Allegro</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/26/02 7:54:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23487.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ2 - Rebirth of the Rogue class</span><hr size=1> Have you seen the AC on bard &quot;plate&quot; armor in EQ?  Hell we are a chain class, it just looks like plate <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br>*edit* - forgot to remove sig <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utenoroallegro.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tenoro Allegro</A> at: 4/26/02 7:54:23 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uackar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ackar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/26/02 11:35:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23487.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ2 - Rebirth of the Rogue class</span><hr size=1> I like the /alias command from UO.<br><br>Couldn't we get something like it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uwulf9.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wulf9</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/27/02 5:40:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23487.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ2 - Rebirth of the Rogue class</span><hr size=1> At this stage of the game the whole armor/AC system is a complete joke.<br><br>In principal though they started out well with two exceptions - Shaman and Rogues should never be able to wear chain.<br><br>Chain armor is HEAVY.  Remarkably flexible for armor but far short of the freedom a rogue would need.  It makes noise when you move.  Whats more it is poor protection against piercing attacks. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/upanolas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Panolas</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_purplespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/27/02 6:31:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23487.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~cyclonis/_uimages/eyes1-3.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ2 - Rebirth of the Rogue class</span><hr size=1> Heres the deal, rogues should be able to wear chain but it should hamper their skills alot, not add to them like it presently does in EQ. <br><br>I'd like to see the game based around more things than just killing mob and getting exp. IMO ultima online had a real fun non combat part of the game but they messed up on the combat part. EQ2 needs to be a combo of both, that would make rogues way more useful. And if they tone down on magic stuff in the game it will make the rogue more like a thief.<br><br>I personally like the idea of a skill based game, it makes the thief we all know and love possible because the theif is the master of skills. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugalendril.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Galendril</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/27/02 8:10:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23487.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ2 - Rebirth of the Rogue class</span><hr size=1> Have mobs drop boxes and chests.  Make these containers locked and/or trapped.<br><br>I played a rogue character in Gemstone III and this was great for rogue desirability in groups.  It was also a good way for making cash in town. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=156063>Galendril Silverdawn</a><BR><a href=http://www.mithrilheartbrigade.org/><i>Mithril Heart Brigade</i></a><BR><BR>Galen<BR><a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/bforgottengrailkeepers><i>Forgotten Grail Keepers</i></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udlaritan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dlaritan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/27/02 9:00:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23487.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ2 - Rebirth of the Rogue class</span><hr size=1> Im going to use a pretext of terms we use in EQ1 to relate an overall picture of what I see the ideal rogue class to be.  IMO the best way to put a rogue class together is <br><br>1) Leather: rogues they need stealth and chain is NOT stealthy, or allow them to use chain, but when they do hide/sneak do not work.<br><br>2) Backstab is FAR too powerful.  You should only be able to land a backstab when you are not on the aggro list.  Backstabs should also land for potentially ALOT MORE damage, but then standard melee output should be capped alot lower... maybe 175 weapon skill caps.  Setting up backstab as a 7 minute refresh discipline may be the only way to truely balance the damage output.  Now this poor melee damage output can be supplimented by meaningful poisions as well.<br><br>Rogues are good melee characters, just not very good and there should be some classes that fall into that category (paladins and sks should be better than rogues in pure toe to toe melee damage).<br><br>In closing, the REAL problem with balance in the game is that class flexibility, or the ability to do ALOT of things, but none of them as well as the next fellow should become far more desireable than it is now.  Backstab, /disc defensive, CH, GoK, Charm and manaburn(lifeburn) are all skills that render the flexibility classes next to useless.  IMO there is not enough of a penalty to the classes that have these game defining abilities.  They should be far more dependant on other characters than they are now.  I dont have a solution, but im pretty sure thats where the real problem with balance lies. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http